##Deep Breath in an epidemic. | I want the baby with me

Micro Signal Xiezuozheyunshegong

FUNCTION INTRODUCTION: Volunteer Information Management, social worker information management, public welfare information release, social work professional exchange

This article is one of the case interviews carried out by the collaborators in the "Peasant Workers' anti-epidemic Rescue Action" , aiming at quickly identifying the vulnerable groups in the epidemic situation and their needs, and providing reference for the epidemic prevention, control and rescue work, we've put together a list to share with you.
Deep breathing in case of an outbreak
A case study of the migrant workers'families in difficulty in Foshan (14)

I want to keep the baby with me
Narrator: Xiao Liao
Place of employment: Xiamen
Editor's Note: Xiao Liao, 35, middle school diploma, no diploma. Home Xinyu, Jiangxi Province, is a single father with a 9-year-old son who stayed home with his grandparents in Xiamen, Fujian Province, where he works as a home improvement company with friends. Xiao Liao stay at home for 10 days on the New Year, but the delay can not start work, can only enter the factory to do handyman, earn some living expenses. Children's learning and growth is the most worrying Liao, the family has no conditions online classes, children can only go to the village committee classes.
I can't go back to work. I got a part-time job

On January 19, I returned home from Fujian for the Lunar New Year. I drove back and forth by myself and stayed at home for 10 days. Because have to go to work, prepare the thing after the worker goes to work, so January 29 returned to Xiamen.

I didn't know about the new pneumonia when I got home, and I didn't know until the next day. It's been a month since I went back to Xiamen. I haven't started yet. I must be stressed, so I found a temporary job, in a factory to do odd jobs, 10 days, daily working hours 8:00-17:30, salary 150 yuan per day. At least we can make ends meet. This job is harder. You have to do everything yourself. Factory hair mask, meals are their own solution, their daily is instant noodles, there is no other to eat.

Our company may not start work until the end of March, and the government hasn't made it clear yet, depending on the outbreak. If you want to start work can, to the municipal government for the letter of guarantee, the risk is larger, we do not dare to get, only to wait until the epidemic normal, can start. We are hired are long-term workers, the types of work, there are about 70 workers, are also at home, did not come back.

Xiao Liao's home (photographed in 2019)

We rent our own house, live in the village, the monthly expenses rent more than 500 yuan, water and electricity more than 100 yuan, eat about 1000 yuan. I normally get paid 4,000 yuan a month, but I haven't started yet. No pay. But the company rented office, warehouse has the cost, depends on Tuba Rabbit to pay 2000 yuan / month guarantee, according to receives the order quantity to want to give the commission. The family annual income 20-30,000, mainly depends on my parents, my money is invested in the company, I do not afford home.

If the company does not start, can maintain 3-4 months, if half a year will lose money.
Internet lessons, the village is also short of equipment

I go home 1-2 times a year, when the holiday is longer, usually like May 1,11, New Year, think of children, and family members.

The TV at home doesn't have online classes, and it still doesn't have an Internet connection, and it says it doesn't have parts.

In the village committee, the children sometimes have no signal. Now my mom drives me around every day, and my dad has to work in the fields, plowing. The child did not wear a mask, the other children in class did not wear a mask, the child finished his homework, he went out to play, there is no other children outside, he just around the village.

I do not know whether the children write homework, mainly do not know the teacher assigned homework, the home does not have a smartphone, the elderly can not use, I generally do not understand the situation in the field.

The outbreak of children in class or the problem was affected in many ways, but parents, teachers can not solve, anxious also useless. For fear of not coming back to work place, also worry about no income, so I returned from home to work place. If I had to choose again, I'd choose to come here. Staying home doesn't help. It is useless to rely on one person. Our village has many children. We can have a class in the village, but this is impossible for us.
I want to keep the baby with me

At present, I am most worried about my son's education, about his physical and mental health, and about learning. He is now and before completely two people, used to lively, now do not like to talk, do not want to communicate with him to answer has been not talking, a bit closed-minded. When I first went to kindergarten, I could write very early, very smart. I guess my ex-wife and I got a divorce, and it's been hard on the kids.

Angels Accompany Liao's children on weekends (2019)

If I can earn money, I would like to stay in Xiamen, better than my hometown. In Xiamen for several years, the old family relations have been estranged, the old family looking for a job is very difficult, Xiamen this side is easier. A friend of mine has moved to Xiamen and his Hukou has also moved here.

The child also needs the suitable environment, if can, next year I want to take the child to Xiamen this side to come to school. My parents don't want to come to Xiamen. I may have to hire a baby-sitter. The main problem is the children to study in Xiamen, the difficulty is a little bit big, social security bought a little late, we do not have social security, want to study here, to pay three years social security, children also. This New Year I brought the Hukou Ben, hope to hand in the Child Social Security in Xiamen, but this period of time epidemic, has been unable to do. Now come to study there is no school can recruit, to find connections, more difficult. I'm looking forward to the epidemic going away, the company taking orders, life going back to normal, and the baby coming to me early.

Social work notes

During the outbreak, Xiao Liao felt helpless in the face of her children's difficulties in attending online classes. On the one hand, the children needed smartphones to attend classes and check homework, and it would have been better if they had stayed at home. On the other hand, there was no income if they stayed at home, and the company spends money every month. In the interview, Xiao Liao hopes that through his efforts, he will be able to bring his children to school, but he also realizes that this is difficult. Social Security, Hukou, etc. will be difficult to achieve in at least three to five years, the child may be about to start middle school... but he is hopeful that he and the child will be reunited soon.
Service advice

Now:
1. Link Resources to help your child with classroom tools and homework assistance so he or she can receive information about lessons and assignments and keep up with the pace of learning
2. TO PROVIDE EPIDEMIC PREVENTION MATERIALS FOR FAMILIES AND PROVIDE EPIDEMIC PREVENTION COUNSELING TO AVOID RISKS;
3. Link Resources, provide children with books, toys, etc. to support children during the epidemic period of learning life as normal as possible.
LONG-TERM:

1. Continue to provide a companion Angel Service, Coordinating Volunteers to provide academic counseling, emotional support and developmental guidance for children;
2. To provide parent-child communication counseling, especially the communication skills in different places, to enhance effective communication between father and son and between generations, and to create a good environment for children to grow up.

I want to keep the baby with me

At present, I am most worried about my son's education, about his physical and mental health, and about learning.
